title: [Gyldemar Green, Forest]
description: Milkweed grows along the forest floor, bees and butterflies hovering around the pale flowers and sampling the nectar.  A small spider spins its web on a nearby branch, hoping one of the nectar eaters will drop in.
Milkweed grows along the forest floor, a favorite of bees and butterflies during the daylight hours.  A small spider spins its web on a nearby branch, hoping one of the nectar eaters will drop in.
